  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0bae\u0bc6\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0b87\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b9c\u0ba4\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0 \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb4\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bbf \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bb2\u0bc8 \u0bae\u0bc1\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0ba9\u0bc6\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbe\u0b95 \u0b9a\u0bc0\u0ba9\u0bbe  \u0b87\u0bb2\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc0\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b85\u0bae\u0bc6\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bbf \u0bb8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0baa\u0ba9\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0baa\u0baf\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0ba4\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "China is using educational institutions in Latin America to advance its soft diplomatic agenda",
      "author": "Rajeeban",
      "body_lines": [
        "China is establishing Chinese educational institutions as a soft diplomatic means to advance its agenda.",
        "The Confucius Institute is seen by many Latin American students as a place where they can learn about Chinese culture and language.",
        "But critics say China is using these schools as soft diplomacy for its agenda.",
        "These teach Mandarin and provide financial assistance for summer camps in China, as well as cultural events and scholarships to study in China, the Hong Kong Post reported.",
        "Jake Hillstrap, who has published a dissertation on Chinese companies in Latin America as a diplomacy for China to advance its agenda, pointed out that China aims to expand these types of educational institutions and that China's intention is to develop future leaders who are closely associated with them and have an understanding of China's culture.",
        "He added that China's views would then be seen as consensual.",
        "Pursibile de Sula, of the Latin American Research Center in China, has expressed fears about the independence of the education sector.",
        "He says the presence and proliferation of Chinese-funded educational institutions could lead to the disappearance of subjects that China does not want.",
        "He noted that the number of Latin American professors in laboratories funded by the Chinese government was high, which would reduce criticism of China in universities.",
        "In a 2019 report on China's risk to educational freedom outside its borders, the International Human Rights Watch warned that the Chinese government could seek to influence academic affairs, monitor foreign students from China, and interfere with educational freedom.",
        "The report also points out that the use of attitudes in the curriculum based on the political intent of banning certain types of topics is similar to the use of existing practices that take into account political allegiance.",
        "The difference between Confucius's institutes and institutions of other languages \u200b\u200bthat teach other languages \u200b\u200bis that the curricula of other countries are not taught in universities, says Gilstrap",
        "The Chinese embassy in Washington, D.C., has told the VOA that Confucius Institute of Studies is an open classroom, and that the laws of Chinese institutions are strictly adhered to.",
        "China has pursued a policy of encouraging state-funded institutions, despite warnings from the United States that the benefits of such institutions could endanger academic freedom. ani"
      ],
